<h3 id="introduction">Introduction</h3>
<p>The letter C is a fundamental component of written language in many
languages, including English. It has various meanings and connotations
depending on its context, such as in names, places, or words like ‘cool’
and ‘complex’. In some cases, the letter C can also be used to represent
sounds in other languages that do not exist in English.</p>
<p>In addition to its significance in written language, the letter C is
also crucial in sign language. The American Sign Language (ASL) alphabet
includes 26 handshapes, each corresponding to a specific letter of the
English alphabet. This manual representation of letters enables
communication between deaf and hearing individuals through visual
means.</p>
