<h3 id="the-letter-in-written-language">The Letter in Written
Language</h3>
<p>The letter C has several functions in written language. It is an
essential part of many words, such as ‘cat’, ‘car’, and ‘computer’. In
phonetics, the letter C represents different sounds depending on its
position within a word. For example, it can indicate a hard sound (/k/)
or a soft sound (/s/). The presence of the letter C also affects the
pronunciation of other letters in a word.</p>
<p>The use of the letter C is widespread across various languages and
cultures. In some languages like French, German, and Italian, the letter
C has its unique sounds and combinations that differ from English. For
instance, the French ‘c’ can be pronounced with a hard or soft sound
depending on whether it’s accompanied by an e.</p>
